channel.title: Ahh Need Expert Help
channel.description: My Cousin, Changed My Ip Address, How do I Change It Back To My Old Ip Address, So I Can Set It Up For My Server?

item.title: Ahh Need Expert Help
item.dc:creator: @Lin Lin
item.description:
@Lin wrote:

Well, if he changed your actual IP address, then go to…

Start > Control Panel > Network Connections > Right click your main internet connect > Properties > Scroll down to Internet Protocol (TCP/IP) and click Properties…

Make sure Obtain an IP Address Automatically is selected, and same thing for the DNS Server.

That just makes it so the IP it obtained automatically, so it should go back to your old one. If not, then change the IP Info in the boxes to match your old one. Make sure Use the following IP address: is selected first.

If this isn’t what you wanted, then let me know.
